President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. held a secure video call with transatlantic leaders to discuss their concern about Russia's military build-up around Ukraine. They expressed support for Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity and emphasized the need for a diplomatic solution to the crisis. The leaders discussed recent engagements with Russia and agreed on the importance of coordinated efforts to deter further Russian aggression. They also committed to imposing severe consequences and economic costs on Russia if it chooses military escalation, as well as reinforcing the defensive posture on NATO's eastern flank. The leaders pledged to maintain close consultation and work through organizations such as NATO, the EU, the OSCE, and the UN. Participants in the call included leaders from Canada, the European Commission, the European Council, France, Germany, Italy, NATO, Poland, Romania, and the United Kingdom.